Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
create_current_region(25.10)                      create_current_region(25.10)

Name
       create_current_region  - Specifies static or dynamic current regions on
       global power-grids over the placed macro to accurately capture high and
       low current consuming regions during rail analysis

Syntax
       create_current_region

       [-help]

       -reset | {-region <x1 y1 x2 y2>

       [-current <value>| -current_pwl_file<filename>]

       [-die_instance_name <dieinstname>]

       [-file <filename>]

       [-label <name>]

       [-layer <layername>]

       [-intrinsic_cap <value>]

       [-loading_cap <value>]

       [-series_resistance<value>]

       [-net<net_name>]

       [-polygon {<x1> <y1> <x2> <y2> <x3> <y3> ..<x1> <y1>}]

       [-pwrnet<net_name>]

       [-gndnet<net_name>]

       }

       Specifies static or dynamic current regions on global power-grids  over
       the  placed  macro to accurately capture high and low current consuming
       regions during rail analysis.

       You can use this command prior to rail analysis to specify current  re-
       gions  or  power  distribution over the top of power-grid on a user-de-
       fined layer. These current regions are generally specified for a placed
       macro  for  which  power-grid  view  library  is  not  available,   and
       power/current  distribution inside this macro could possibly impact IR-
       drop in neighboring regions. These current regions can also be  defined
       over  top-level power-grid for an unplaced macro during early stages of
       power-planning.

Parameters
       -current <value>
              In the static mode (set_rail_analysis_mode -method static),  the
              parameter specifies a single current value in mAmp.

              In the dynamic mode (set_rail_analysis_mode -method dynamic) the
              parameter  specifies  a PWL current waveform in time (in ns) and
              current (in mA) format. For example, 0ns 0mA 0.5ns 1mA  1ns  2mA
              3ns 1mA 4ns 0.

       -current_pwl_file<filename>
              Specifies a PWL current file. The file has two columns, time (in
              ns) and current value (in mA), as shown below:

              time1 value1

              time2 value2

              The  -current_pwl_file and  -current parameters are mutually ex-
              clusive.

       -die_instance_name <dieinstname>
              Specifies  the name of the die to which you need to apply a cur-
              rent region. This parameter is only applicable to the  multi-die
              analysis flow (set_rail_analysis_mode -die_mode multi-die).

              The  parameter  allows you to accurately assign current to power
              and ground nets in specific  geometric  regions  for  individual
              dies during rail analysis in 3D-IC designs.

       -file <filename>
              Specifies  the name of a file containing the list of current re-
              gions for each die. -file can be used only  with  the   -die_in-
              stance_name  parameter. The other parameters of the  create_cur-
              rent_region command can be included within the specified file.

              Example:

              create_current_region   -file   <create_current_region_die0.tcl>
              -die_instance_name Die0

              create_current_region   -file   <create_current_region_die1.tcl>
              -die_instance_name Die1

              ###File content in <create_current_region_die0.tcl>

              -net VDD -current  50mA -layer M2 -region "10 10 100 100"

              -net VDD -current  50mA -layer M2 -region "100 100 200 200"

              -net VSS -current  100mA -layer M1 -region "10 10 200 200"

              ###File content in <create_current_region_die1.tcl>

              -net VDD -current  150mA -layer M2 -region "10 10 50 50"

              -net VDD -current  50mA -layer M2 -region "100 100 200 200"

              -net VSS -current  200mA -layer M1 -region "10 10 200 200"

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each create_current_region parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command man create_current_region.

       -gndnet<net_name>
              Specifies a ground net name on which the specified current is to
              be applied.

       -intrinsic_cap <value>
              Specifies  the  cell  intrinsic capacitance in pico farads (pf).
              This  is  required  parameter  when  set  in  the  dynamic  mode
              (set_rail_analysis_mode -method dynamic). This parameter is dis-
              abled in static mode.

       -label <name>
              Specifies a name to a specific current region. The parameter al-
              lows  to  assign  a user-specific name to the region, instead of
              using the default name generated by the  tool.  By  assigning  a
              unique name, you can easily identify and manage the regions. For
              instance, instead of having generic names like "Region 1," using
              specific names like "VDD_area1" or "VSS_area2" can provide imme-
              diate context.

       -layer <layername>
              Specifies a layer name on which the scaling will be performed.

              Multiple  commands can be issued to scale resistance on multiple
              layers. This is a required parameter.

       -loading_cap value
              Specifies the cell loading capacitance in pico farads (pf). This
              is  required  parameter   when   set   in   the   dynamic   mode
              (set_rail_analysis_mode -method dynamic). This parameter is dis-
              abled in static mode.

       -net<net_name>
              Specifies a net name on which the specified current is to be ap-
              plied.

       -polygon {<x1> <y1> <x2> <y2> <x3> <y3> ..<x1> <y1>}
              Specifies a rectilinear current region where the current will be
              distributed  within. The rectilinear region enables you to spec-
              ify multiple x,y points to add current regions in the areas that
              are not rectangular in shape.

              When specified, the last xy coordinate location will be the same
              as the first xy location. The xy  coordinates  will  be  in  the
              counterclockwise sequence.

       -pwrnet<net_name>
              Specifies  a power net name on which the specified current is to
              be applied.

       -region <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              Specifies the region on the layer  across  which  the  specified
              current  and capacitance (in dynamic mode) is distributed by the
              rail analysis engine. The units of x and y should be in microns.

              This is a required parameter.

       -reset Resets all the previous create_current_region command settings.

       -series_resistance<value>
              Specifies the series resistance (ESR) value attached to each tap
              point in the current region definition.

Examples
              * The following command specifies static current region:

                create_current_region -current 2mA -layer METAL_1 -region "100
                100 200 200"

              * The following command specifies dynamic current region:

                create_current_region -current {0ns 0mA 0.5ns 1mA 1ns 2mA  3ns
                1mA  4ns  0} -layer METAL_1 -region "200 200 400 400" -intrin-
                sic_cap 40 -loading_cap 20

              * The following command resets all create_current_region parame-
                ters to their default values:

                create_current_region -reset

              * The following command specifies  rectilinear  current  regions
                for die instance Die1:

                create_current_region  -net  VDD  -current  50mA -layer Metal5
                -polygon "10 10 100 10  100  100  10  100  10  10  "  -die_in-
                stance_name Die1

                create_current_region  -net  VDD  -current  50mA -layer Metal5
                -polygon "100 100 200 100 200 200 100 200  100  100"  -die_in-
                stance_name Die1

              * The following command specifies the static current region with
                the region name VDD_area1:

                create_current_region  -label  VDD_area1 -region "0.0 0.0 87.3
                107.2" -layer M1 -current 1 mA -net VDD

